snippet: Three years ago Texans defensive end J. J. Watt could be found at a Pizza Hut, telling people that he would play for Wisconsin and in the N.F.L. someday.
abstract: Houston Texans defensive end J J Watt etched his name in franchise lore with interception return for a touchdown in Houston's AFC wild-card victory over Cincinnati Bengals; win was the Texans first playoff appearance in franchise's 10-year history.
lead_paragraph: Three years ago Texans defensive end J. J. Watt could be found at a Pizza Hut, telling people that he would play for Wisconsin and in the N.F.L. someday.

headline.seo: Texans’ J.J. Watt Makes Play as Big as His Dreams
headline.main: Texans Rookie Makes a Play as Big as His Dreams
headline.print_headline: Texans Rookie Makes a Play as Big as His Dreams
